React setup
Install node js (backend env)
Install VS Studio
Create a new React folder and open in VS Studio
Open terminal in VS Studio and run the commands
npm create vite@latest
give a project name ex. my-react-app
select React then javascript
cd my-react-app
npm install
npm run dev
Server is running now and can be accessed via the localhost:port link

import React, {useState} from 'react';
const [var, setVar] = useState(initialVal);
const updateName = () => {
        setVar("New Val");
    }
use className instead of class(reserved)
<> code </> wrap code with fragment to return more than one element


